I make this almost weekly. It's definitely a family favorite. I modify it a bit, partly because my son is allergic to milk and partly because I keep a lot of the ingredients on hand. I usually double the recipe so we can have extras. I find that it's a lot better this way: I use only coconut milk (not the lite version), a full jar of Major Grey's Chutney (I've also used apricot preserves when I was out of chutney - worked fine, but is better with the chutney because of the extra spices in it) and canned diced tomatoes (my husband made this recently when I was out and used fresh...strangely, it wasn't as good). I also slice the onions rather thick so they don't melt away. Enjoy!

