Excellent flavour. The spice combination is the key. I've noticed however that when I visit an East Indian restaurant, the sauces are often quite smooth in texture. Therefore, when making this dish, after browning the meat and removing from the pan, I then brown the onions, and combine the tomatoes, milk etc. I put the mixture thru my blender to achieve a smooth consistency. I then recombine the liquids with the spices and meat before slow cooking it for @ 4 hours. The flavour is fantastic and my husband told me 'I certainly have outdone myself'.

