Rating: 4
This is a total keeper of a recipe. I can totally see making this a once a week dish. The beef was good but any meat would be great, particularly lamb. I read through dozens of other posts with adjustments and incorporated many of them. Here is how I did it; Adjustments; As per other suggestions wanted to increase the sauce, texture and color of the dish Cooked 3/4 of onions before adding all other ingredients. Added the last 1/4 once everything was together and brought to simmer Used (3) cans of organic diced, peeled tomatoes. Added two cans when the recipe called for tomatoes and added the last can 3/4 through the cooking process Used a can of coconut milk. Definitely look for the light version to keep it healthy. Also 1/2 a can of water. Substituted the 1/4 teaspoon of crushed dried pepper for 3 tbsp of prepared Madras Curry Paste. These prepared pastes are readily available and cheap. They add much more dimension of flavor due to the extra spices. Omitted the Chutney. We didn't miss it. Only used one cinnamon stick. I served it garnished with lots of fresh chopped cilantro, Basmati rice (sure fire prep method on this site) and nan bread. Big Hit!

