Rating: 4
I agree with all of the reviews so far. This is really a spectacular recipe. The broth has SO much character I really felt like a pro when I made this for my girlfriend. And she is a tough critic, I dare say a food snob. I have two recommendations for this recipe, however. My first is that if you enjoy curry broth, increase the ingredients that pertain to the broth in this recipe. Then you'll have extra to soak into the rice. Second, I recommend adding the onions and tomatos much LATER in the ripe to prevent them from turning to mush. While I understand that monosodium glutamate (sp?) in tomatoes adds to the flavor of just about any savory dish, no one wants a pile of mushy mush in their bowl of curry. So I recommend allowing the beef to become completely tender before adding either the tomatoes or onions. Adding peppers or carrots isn't a bad idea either, especially if you heed my advice and increase the amount of broth.

