I also greatly enjoyed this recipe and will definitely make it again. Both for dietary reasons and because I didn't have any chutney, I substituted mango/apricot yoghurt for the milk (coconut milk) and chutney in the recipe. Like so many others, I too used some diced tomatoes (really valuable, I'm sure, in ensuring that the curry stays moist during long cooking times). But I also cut up some regular tomatoes too, for added texture. About a half-hour before taking off the heat, I also added mushrooms. Obviously, the amount of curry powder and/or red pepper is a matter of personal taste. This is going to sound somewhat silly, but don't forget to let people know not to eat the cinnamon stick (or take it out before serving). Enjoy!!

